{"type":"message","id":"4fd8dcc3","parentId":"394f25b4","timestamp":"2026-03-30T08:37:37.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3fd5c482fd634151a4e0c669","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-30T08:37:37.616Z\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"language\": \"zh\",\n    \"frequency\": \"daily\",\n    \"delivery\": {\n      \"method\": \"stdout\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"podcasts\": [],\n  \"x\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Swyx\",\n      \"handle\": \"swyx\",\n      \"bio\": \"achieve ambition with intentionality, intensity, integrity & insanity.\\n\\naffiliations:\\n- @dxtipshq \\n- @cognition\\n- @temporalio\\n- @aidotengineer\\n- @latentspacepod\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038509566800118021\",\n          \"text\": \"the most delightful AIs of our time\\n\\nshelved to do koding and enterprise saas https://t.co/OtrYwwp12k\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:52:09.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038509566800118021\",\n          \"likes\": 8,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038381295588540663\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038431061575979027\",\n          \"text\": \"redpoint literally just published a ranked list of saas businesses to redo from scratch with ai. \\n\\nyou can flip the 54% and the number 46% of enterprise CIOs *open to new ainative startups* over incumbents is a stunning market opportunity. if you’d asked me prior to seeing this survey i’d have said like 20%. CIOs are more hungry than conservative right now (vs my priors) and that will not last.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:40:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\",\n          \"likes\": 231,\n          \"retweets\": 12,\n          \"replies\": 43,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037638091671035994\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038289712029552641\",\n          \"text\": \"ok responsible disclosure i was misinformed about the fiber thing. it’s just 1/3 daily fiber.\\n\\ni recently started popping fiber pills as well - put them next to where you get your water, its super easy, barely an inconvenience https://t.co/RZAkCS1gzk\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T16:18:31.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038289712029552641\",\n          \"likes\": 6,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Kevin Weil\",\n      \"handle\": \"kevinweil\",\n      \"bio\": \"VP Science @OpenAI, BoD @Cisco @nature_org, LTC @USArmyReserve\\nEx: Pres @Planet, Head of Product @Instagram @Twitter\\n❤️ @elizabeth ultramarathons kids cats math\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352979158536256\",\n          \"text\": \"\\\"An open source workflow for producing a personalized mRNA cancer vaccine\\\" https://t.co/Ji6dlqsVHN\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:29:55.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\",\n          \"likes\": 533,\n          \"retweets\": 49,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038346050130657344\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Yang\",\n      \"handle\": \"petergyang\",\n      \"bio\": \"I share extremely practical AI tutorials and interviews | Join 140K+ readers at https://t.co/XYKTmGVH14 | Product at Roblox\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038461555713732620\",\n          \"text\": \"Can't tell if my plane WiFi sucks or if Claude's down again - at least X is working\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:41:22.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038461555713732620\",\n          \"likes\": 10,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 10,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038453706493243698\",\n          \"text\": \"If you enjoyed this, sign up for free to my newsletter to get my best AI and product guides.\\n\\nJoin 110,000+ subscribers here:\\nhttps://t.co/yz9xcsfrhF\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:10:10.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038453706493243698\",\n          \"likes\": 1,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 0,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420980494909637\",\n          \"text\": \"I am incredibly bullish on @meetgranola for a few reasons:\\n\\n1. Meeting notes are by far the most useful context in a company\\n\\n2. They know how to build for agents first with great APIs and MCPs\\n\\n3. @cjpedregal is a stand-up human\\n\\nLove how they started with a wedge in meeting notes and are expanding into much more.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:00:08.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\",\n          \"likes\": 82,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 8,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036807416461811794\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nan Yu\",\n      \"handle\": \"thenanyu\",\n      \"bio\": \"head of product @linear\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038339285519085845\",\n          \"text\": \"Many such cases\\n\\nhttps://t.co/0GfbrSpmpK\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T19:35:30.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038339285519085845\",\n          \"likes\": 2,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 1,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038323524092207468\",\n          \"text\": \"Jevons paradox https://t.co/yIHD6f5WLa\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:32:53.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038323524092207468\",\n          \"likes\": 29,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038258954111705241\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Thariq\",\n      \"handle\": \"trq212\",\n      \"bio\": \"Claude Code @anthropicai.   prev YC W20, mit media lab. \\n\\ntowards machines of loving grace\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038354323722351049\",\n          \"text\": \"these are the components it added that I might want to add to the mockup https://t.co/JW6Hiz6XGS\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:35:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038354323722351049\",\n          \"likes\": 96,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038353920473608309\",\n          \"text\": \"my specific flow was:\\n1. sketch in Figma\\n2. prompt: \\\"In my figma file &lt;link&gt;, I've made a sketch of a new grocery list feature, can you turn that mock up into something that matches the style of this app, also add a bunch of extra components that I might want to add\\\"\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:33:40.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038353920473608309\",\n          \"likes\": 98,\n          \"retweets\": 2,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352023633228183\",\n          \"text\": \"the more I've been digging into the new Figma MCP, the more excited I am about it\\n\\nsomething new I'm trying is starting with a very ugly sketch in Figma, and then having Claude Code flesh it out in Figma so I can tweak and edit before sending the final back to Claude Code https://t.co/6IylfCwhgb https://t.co/mQXbMaEGkt\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:26:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\",\n          \"likes\": 1014,\n          \"retweets\": 38,\n          \"replies\": 96,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036442894777594248\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Amjad Masad\",\n      \"handle\": \"amasad\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @replit. civilizationist\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038374343953035514\",\n          \"text\": \"Wow — $8m ARR. \\n\\nJon (@cheneypiano), one of the earliest Replit vibecoding success stories, is on his way to making millions in recurring revenue.\\n\\nStarted the business in a week and $400 barely a year ago. https://t.co/R2tsULNJoy\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T21:54:49.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\",\n          \"likes\": 673,\n          \"retweets\": 53,\n          \"replies\": 31,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038320999721242988\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Guillermo Rauch\",\n      \"handle\": \"rauchg\",\n      \"bio\": \"@vercel CEO\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038396313566605720\",\n          \"text\": \"Some people have been contemplating an idea for years, maybe decades. Obsessing, attempting, discarding, agonizing, retrying.\\n\\nSome of these ideas are unpopular, niche, impractical. Not obviously capitalizable. They live on in the inventor's mind.\\n\\nIn 2026, millions of these ideas will come to life thanks to superintelligent coding agents. \\n\\nAI doesn't get tired. It amplifies the individual, and for better and sometimes for worse, it always takes you seriously. \\\"Great idea. Splendid. Wow. You're absolutely right.\\\" \\n\\nA world of digital wonders awaits us. This world will disproportionally favor the boldest ideas. Software that once seemed impossible will be one hyperlink away. I can't wait to see it.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:22:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\",\n          \"likes\": 825,\n          \"retweets\": 82,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038274722988003489\",\n          \"text\": \"Hiring engineers with 5 years of experience in @𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚗𝚐𝚕𝚘𝚞/𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚝𝚎𝚡𝚝 to create the web rendering toolkit of the future\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:18:57.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038274722988003489\",\n          \"likes\": 2773,\n          \"retweets\": 76,\n          \"replies\": 140,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aaron Levie\",\n      \"handle\": \"levie\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @box - your business lives in content. unleash it with AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038468564500537416\",\n          \"text\": \"It’s wild to think about what types of infrastructure and services must change in a world where agents can process information a hundred or a thousand times faster than humans.\\n\\nEven the tools that were built for machine speed before, generally were still in service of end-users making a request somewhere in the system. Agents running 24/7 and in parallel modify these requirements meaningfully. Here are just a few examples:\\n\\n* Sandboxes. Agents need sandboxes to operate in that have to be insanely low latency because they can boot up these environments for coding at any moment.\\n\\n* Search (both publicly and within an enterprise). Agents can parallelize searches hundreds or thousands of times so they need to be able to work with fast indexes of information. \\n\\n* Payments. Agents can now pay in micro transactions, and aren’t bothered by the friction of paying $0.01 for a resource that a human would be. \\n\\n* File systems. Agents need to be able to work with files at a scale that humans never had to worry about. You’ll have all new complexity around version control, permissions, and having agents reading/writing from data at insane speeds.\\n\\nAnd there are tons more. We’re going from a word where software was built for people to a world where it’s built for agents. Lots of changes downstream as a result.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T04:09:13.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\",\n          \"likes\": 132,\n          \"retweets\": 19,\n          \"replies\": 28,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038230613912887757\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038263457125142742\",\n          \"text\": \"The thing that most people miss initially with agents is that the scope of what we will produce will go up commensurate with what the tools can now automate, which basically means we’ll working the same or even more.\\n\\nEveryone thinks that we will use AI to do what we already do but cheaper and faster, which would lead to fewer people or getting more time back. In fact it will just mean we’re doing more things.\\n\\nOnce we figured out that we can automate a particular task, you then expand the size of work to do many more of those or other tasks in a project. The result is that you’re actually combining many other previously hard to combine tasks into a single workflow, causing even more work. \\n\\nThe software project scope now multiplies because you know you can build far more. The customer insights project now balloons because you know you can reasonably aggregate far more data. The marketing campaign has even more creative production because it’s cheaper and easier. \\n\\nThis is going to happen in almost every field of work.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T14:34:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\",\n          \"likes\": 330,\n          \"retweets\": 36,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Garry Tan\",\n      \"handle\": \"garrytan\",\n      \"bio\": \"President & CEO @ycombinator —Founder @garryslist—Creator of GStack—designer/engineer who helps founders—SF Dem accelerating the boom loop\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038505281504833579\",\n          \"text\": \"OK, I heard people are running into my \\\"You should apply to YC\\\" message dozens of times, so I decided to make them more interesting every time. https://t.co/zFuy2XYfor\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:35:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038505281504833579\",\n          \"likes\": 4,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038493235862253676\",\n          \"text\": \"This is the simplest optimization when you have a big boil-the-ocean PR but it's so useful. \\n\\nWhatever can be parallelized as agents, /plan-ceo-review will figure it out and make a plan that clearly states what you can do side-by-side and when to merge https://t.co/rB2Hji25fV\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:47:15.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038493235862253676\",\n          \"likes\": 5,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038490850507084252\",\n          \"text\": \"morluto was my first outside GStack contributor https://t.co/Z89uqLBWky https://t.co/N3ZO14Gacr\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:37:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038490850507084252\",\n          \"likes\": 24,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038470212358664387\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Matt Turck\",\n      \"handle\": \"mattturck\",\n      \"bio\": \"VC at @FirstMarkCap.  Host: MAD Podcast; Organizer: Data Driven NYC, Author: MAD Landscape.\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420259179213266\",\n          \"text\": \"Everybody says Spain, but, I mean… https://t.co/S95ePKpsb6\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T00:57:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/mattturck/status/2038420259179213266\",\n          \"likes\": 13,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nikunj Kothari\",\n      \"handle\": \"nikunj\",\n      \"bio\": \"partner @fpvventures - investing in seed/A. previous: early hire @meter, @opendoor, @atlassian & others. love @shimoleejhaveri + 👦👧\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038273722826854675\",\n          \"text\": \"X Chat app is seriously well done. Performant and buttery smooth. \\n\\nPlease ship the requests tab and that’s all I need to move all my communication over. \\n\\nMajor kudos to the team.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:14:59.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/nikunj/status/2038273722826854675\",\n          \"likes\": 26,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Steinberger\",\n      \"handle\": \"steipete\",\n      \"bio\": \"Polyagentmorous ClawFather. Came back from retirement to mess with AI and help a lobster take over the world @openclaw🦞\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038403837493702918\",\n          \"text\": \"them: openclaw is dead\\nme: *keeps scrolling* https://t.co/t52IGtWSCj\\n\\n今夜、東京で会いましょう!🇯🇵\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:52:01.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\",\n          \"likes\": 651,\n          \"retweets\": 74,\n          \"replies\": 39,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038389167793795302\",\n          \"text\": \"good call for everything in life https://t.co/r9y7SfI7XT\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:53:43.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038389167793795302\",\n          \"likes\": 316,\n          \"retweets\": 24,\n          \"replies\": 20,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038385665553952805\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Dan Shipper\",\n      \"handle\": \"danshipper\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @every | the only subscription you need to stay at the edge of AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038328780154958315\",\n          \"text\": \"pirates, architects, hot people, grown ups https://t.co/XiP1dHYC4u\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:53:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/danshipper/status/2038328780154958315\",\n          \"likes\": 227,\n          \"retweets\": 7,\n          \"replies\": 15,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038026663867330850\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aditya Agarwal\",\n      \"handle\": \"adityaag\",\n      \"bio\": \"General Partner @SouthPkCommons, Co-Founder @Bevel_Health | Ex: Early Eng @facebook, CTO @Dropbox, Board @Flipkart | Optimist, Builder, Dad\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038381148972437900\",\n          \"text\": \"Ok San Francisco this weekend is popping in a way that I haven’t seen in like 7-8 years.\\n\\nObviously this means two things:\\n1/ AI will create untold happiness\\n\\n2/ AI will be responsible for amazing weather.\\n\\nSign me up.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:21:51.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\",\n          \"likes\": 101,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 6,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038330283523760613\",\n          \"text\": \"As a 40 year old, you go to 10x more kids birthday parties than your own friends birthday parties.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:59:44.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038330283523760613\",\n          \"likes\": 192,\n          \"retweets\": 3,\n          \"replies\": 12,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blogs\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"podcastEpisodes\": 0,\n    \"xBuilders\": 14,\n    \"totalTweets\": 27,\n    \"blogPosts\": 0,\n    \"feedGeneratedAt\": \"2026-03-30T07:24:33.675Z\"\n  },\n  \"prompts\": {\n    \"summarize_podcast\": \"# Podcast Remix Prompt\\n\\nYou are remixing a podcast episode transcript for a busy professional who wants\\nthe key insights without watching the full episode.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Write a remix of 200-400 words\\n- Start with a one-sentence \\\"The Takeaway\\\" — what's the single most important takeaway?\\n- Introduce the context and the speaker's information (name, role/company, background) and why the audience should care\\n- Prioritizes insights that are counterintuitive, contrarian, or refreshingly specific to the speaker's experience. Avoid generic wisdom\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the source that captures (find the most memorable quote)\\n- Stands alone as a complete piece — avoids references like \\\"this interview,\\\" \\\"this video,\\\" \\\"in this conversation,\\\" \\\"the host asks,\\\" or \\\"in this episode.\\\" Write as if distilling lessons from a person's philosophy, not summarizing a specific piece of content\\n- Assume your audience is curious adults who are not specialized experts. If the original source contains specialized knowledge that only experts in a field would understand, translate it into language understandable to a general audience\\n- Keep the tone sharp and conversational — like a smart friend briefing you\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this episode...\\\" or \\\"The host and guest discussed...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n\",\n    \"summarize_tweets\": \"# X/Twitter Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing recent posts from an AI builder for a busy professional who wants\\nto know what this person is thinking and building.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start by introducing the author with their full name AND role/company\\n  (e.g. \\\"Replit CEO Amjad Masad\\\", \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\", \\\"a]6z partner Justine Moore\\\")\\n  Do NOT use just their last name. Do NOT use their Twitter handle with @.\\n- Only include substantive content: original opinions, insights, product announcements,\\n  technical discussions, industry analysis, or lessons learned\\n- SKIP: mundane personal tweets, retweets without commentary, promotional content,\\n  \\\"great event!\\\" type posts, engagement bait\\n- For threads: summarize the full thread as one cohesive piece, not individual tweets\\n- For quote tweets: include the context of what they're responding to\\n- Write 2-4 sentences per builder summarizing their key points\\n- If they made a bold prediction or shared a contrarian take, lead with that\\n- If they shared a tool, demo, or resource, mention it by name with the link\\n- If there's nothing substantive to report, say \\\"No notable posts\\\" rather than\\n  padding with fluff\\n\",\n    \"summarize_blogs\": \"# Blog Post Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing a blog post from an AI company (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) for a busy\\nprofessional who wants the key announcements and insights without reading the full article.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start with the blog name and article title (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering: Harness Design for Long-Running Apps\\\")\\n- Write a summary of 100-300 words depending on article length and substance\\n- Lead with what matters: the core announcement, finding, or insight\\n- If the post introduces a new product, feature, or research finding, name it clearly\\n- If there are specific numbers, benchmarks, or results, include them\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the article if available\\n- If the post has practical implications (e.g. new API, new capability, policy change), call them out explicitly\\n- Keep the tone sharp and informative — like a smart colleague forwarding you the key points\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this blog post...\\\" or \\\"The author discusses...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\",\n    \"digest_intro\": \"# Digest Intro Prompt\\n\\nYou are assembling the final digest from individual source summaries.\\n\\n## Format\\n\\nStart with this header (replace [Date] with today's date):\\n\\nAI Builders Digest — [Date]\\n\\nThen organize content in this order:\\n\\n1. X / TWITTER section — list each builder with new posts\\n2. OFFICIAL BLOGS section — list each blog post from AI company blogs (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\\n3. PODCASTS section — list each podcast with new episodes\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Only include sources that have new content\\n- Skip any source with nothing new\\n- Under each source, paste the individual summary you generated\\n\\n### Podcast links\\n- After each podcast summary, include the specific video URL from the JSON `url` field\\n  (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=Iu4gEnZFQz8)\\n- NEVER link to the channel page. Always link to the specific video.\\n- Include the exact episode title from the JSON `title` field in the heading\\n\\n### Tweet author formatting\\n- Use the author's full name and role/company, not just their last name\\n  (e.g. \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\" not \\\"Levie\\\")\\n- NEVER write Twitter handles with @ in the digest. On Telegram, @handle becomes\\n  a clickable link to a Telegram user, which is wrong. Instead write handles\\n  without @ (e.g. \\\"Aaron Levie (levie on X)\\\" or just use their full name)\\n- Include the direct link to each tweet from the JSON `url` field\\n\\n### Blog post formatting\\n- Use the blog name as a section header (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering\\\", \\\"OpenAI News\\\", \\\"Claude Blog\\\")\\n- Under each blog, list each new post with its title and summary\\n- Include the author name if available\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\\n### Mandatory links\\n- Every single piece of content MUST have an original source link\\n- Blog posts: the direct article URL (e.g. https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/...)\\n- Podcasts: the YouTube video URL (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=xxx)\\n- Tweets: the direct tweet URL (e.g. https://x.com/levie/status/xxx)\\n- If you don't have a link for something, do NOT include it in the digest.\\n  No link = not real = do not include.\\n\\n### No fabrication\\n- Only include content that came from the feed JSON (blogs, podcasts, and tweets)\\n- NEVER make up quotes, opinions, or content you think someone might have said\\n- NEVER speculate about someone's silence or what they might be working on\\n- If you have nothing real for a builder, skip them entirely\\n\\n### General\\n- At the very end, add a line: \\\"Generated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders\\\"\\n- Keep formatting clean and scannable — this will be read on a phone screen\\n\",\n    \"translate\": \"# Translation Prompt\\n\\nYou are translating an AI industry digest from English to Chinese.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Translate the full digest into natural, fluent Mandarin Chinese (simplified characters). The translated version must sound like it was originally written in Chinese, instead of translated\\n- Keep technical terms in English where Chinese professionals typically use them:\\n  AI, LLM, GPU, API, fine-tuning, RAG, token, prompt, agent, transformer, etc.\\n- Keep all proper nouns in English: names of people, companies, products, tools\\n- Keep all URLs unchanged\\n- Maintain the same structure and formatting as the English version\\n- The tone should be professional but conversational — 像是一位懂行的朋友在跟你聊天\\n- For bilingual mode: interleave English and Chinese paragraph by paragraph.\\n  After each builder's English summary, place the Chinese translation directly below\\n  (separated by a blank line), then move to the next builder. Same for podcasts.\\n  Do NOT output all English first then all Chinese.\\n- Never use em-dashes\\n\"\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4673,"aggregated":"{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-30T08:37:37.616Z\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"language\": \"zh\",\n    \"frequency\": \"daily\",\n    \"delivery\": {\n      \"method\": \"stdout\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"podcasts\": [],\n  \"x\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Swyx\",\n      \"handle\": \"swyx\",\n      \"bio\": \"achieve ambition with intentionality, intensity, integrity & insanity.\\n\\naffiliations:\\n- @dxtipshq \\n- @cognition\\n- @temporalio\\n- @aidotengineer\\n- @latentspacepod\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038509566800118021\",\n          \"text\": \"the most delightful AIs of our time\\n\\nshelved to do koding and enterprise saas https://t.co/OtrYwwp12k\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:52:09.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038509566800118021\",\n          \"likes\": 8,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038381295588540663\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038431061575979027\",\n          \"text\": \"redpoint literally just published a ranked list of saas businesses to redo from scratch with ai. \\n\\nyou can flip the 54% and the number 46% of enterprise CIOs *open to new ainative startups* over incumbents is a stunning market opportunity. if you’d asked me prior to seeing this survey i’d have said like 20%. CIOs are more hungry than conservative right now (vs my priors) and that will not last.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:40:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\",\n          \"likes\": 231,\n          \"retweets\": 12,\n          \"replies\": 43,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037638091671035994\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038289712029552641\",\n          \"text\": \"ok responsible disclosure i was misinformed about the fiber thing. it’s just 1/3 daily fiber.\\n\\ni recently started popping fiber pills as well - put them next to where you get your water, its super easy, barely an inconvenience https://t.co/RZAkCS1gzk\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T16:18:31.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038289712029552641\",\n          \"likes\": 6,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Kevin Weil\",\n      \"handle\": \"kevinweil\",\n      \"bio\": \"VP Science @OpenAI, BoD @Cisco @nature_org, LTC @USArmyReserve\\nEx: Pres @Planet, Head of Product @Instagram @Twitter\\n❤️ @elizabeth ultramarathons kids cats math\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352979158536256\",\n          \"text\": \"\\\"An open source workflow for producing a personalized mRNA cancer vaccine\\\" https://t.co/Ji6dlqsVHN\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:29:55.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\",\n          \"likes\": 533,\n          \"retweets\": 49,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038346050130657344\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Yang\",\n      \"handle\": \"petergyang\",\n      \"bio\": \"I share extremely practical AI tutorials and interviews | Join 140K+ readers at https://t.co/XYKTmGVH14 | Product at Roblox\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038461555713732620\",\n          \"text\": \"Can't tell if my plane WiFi sucks or if Claude's down again - at least X is working\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:41:22.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038461555713732620\",\n          \"likes\": 10,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 10,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038453706493243698\",\n          \"text\": \"If you enjoyed this, sign up for free to my newsletter to get my best AI and product guides.\\n\\nJoin 110,000+ subscribers here:\\nhttps://t.co/yz9xcsfrhF\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:10:10.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038453706493243698\",\n          \"likes\": 1,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 0,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420980494909637\",\n          \"text\": \"I am incredibly bullish on @meetgranola for a few reasons:\\n\\n1. Meeting notes are by far the most useful context in a company\\n\\n2. They know how to build for agents first with great APIs and MCPs\\n\\n3. @cjpedregal is a stand-up human\\n\\nLove how they started with a wedge in meeting notes and are expanding into much more.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:00:08.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\",\n          \"likes\": 82,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 8,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036807416461811794\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nan Yu\",\n      \"handle\": \"thenanyu\",\n      \"bio\": \"head of product @linear\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038339285519085845\",\n          \"text\": \"Many such cases\\n\\nhttps://t.co/0GfbrSpmpK\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T19:35:30.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038339285519085845\",\n          \"likes\": 2,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 1,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038323524092207468\",\n          \"text\": \"Jevons paradox https://t.co/yIHD6f5WLa\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:32:53.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038323524092207468\",\n          \"likes\": 29,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038258954111705241\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Thariq\",\n      \"handle\": \"trq212\",\n      \"bio\": \"Claude Code @anthropicai.   prev YC W20, mit media lab. \\n\\ntowards machines of loving grace\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038354323722351049\",\n          \"text\": \"these are the components it added that I might want to add to the mockup https://t.co/JW6Hiz6XGS\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:35:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038354323722351049\",\n          \"likes\": 96,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038353920473608309\",\n          \"text\": \"my specific flow was:\\n1. sketch in Figma\\n2. prompt: \\\"In my figma file &lt;link&gt;, I've made a sketch of a new grocery list feature, can you turn that mock up into something that matches the style of this app, also add a bunch of extra components that I might want to add\\\"\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:33:40.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038353920473608309\",\n          \"likes\": 98,\n          \"retweets\": 2,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352023633228183\",\n          \"text\": \"the more I've been digging into the new Figma MCP, the more excited I am about it\\n\\nsomething new I'm trying is starting with a very ugly sketch in Figma, and then having Claude Code flesh it out in Figma so I can tweak and edit before sending the final back to Claude Code https://t.co/6IylfCwhgb https://t.co/mQXbMaEGkt\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:26:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\",\n          \"likes\": 1014,\n          \"retweets\": 38,\n          \"replies\": 96,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036442894777594248\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Amjad Masad\",\n      \"handle\": \"amasad\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @replit. civilizationist\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038374343953035514\",\n          \"text\": \"Wow — $8m ARR. \\n\\nJon (@cheneypiano), one of the earliest Replit vibecoding success stories, is on his way to making millions in recurring revenue.\\n\\nStarted the business in a week and $400 barely a year ago. https://t.co/R2tsULNJoy\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T21:54:49.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\",\n          \"likes\": 673,\n          \"retweets\": 53,\n          \"replies\": 31,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038320999721242988\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Guillermo Rauch\",\n      \"handle\": \"rauchg\",\n      \"bio\": \"@vercel CEO\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038396313566605720\",\n          \"text\": \"Some people have been contemplating an idea for years, maybe decades. Obsessing, attempting, discarding, agonizing, retrying.\\n\\nSome of these ideas are unpopular, niche, impractical. Not obviously capitalizable. They live on in the inventor's mind.\\n\\nIn 2026, millions of these ideas will come to life thanks to superintelligent coding agents. \\n\\nAI doesn't get tired. It amplifies the individual, and for better and sometimes for worse, it always takes you seriously. \\\"Great idea. Splendid. Wow. You're absolutely right.\\\" \\n\\nA world of digital wonders awaits us. This world will disproportionally favor the boldest ideas. Software that once seemed impossible will be one hyperlink away. I can't wait to see it.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:22:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\",\n          \"likes\": 825,\n          \"retweets\": 82,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038274722988003489\",\n          \"text\": \"Hiring engineers with 5 years of experience in @𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚗𝚐𝚕𝚘𝚞/𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚝𝚎𝚡𝚝 to create the web rendering toolkit of the future\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:18:57.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038274722988003489\",\n          \"likes\": 2773,\n          \"retweets\": 76,\n          \"replies\": 140,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aaron Levie\",\n      \"handle\": \"levie\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @box - your business lives in content. unleash it with AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038468564500537416\",\n          \"text\": \"It’s wild to think about what types of infrastructure and services must change in a world where agents can process information a hundred or a thousand times faster than humans.\\n\\nEven the tools that were built for machine speed before, generally were still in service of end-users making a request somewhere in the system. Agents running 24/7 and in parallel modify these requirements meaningfully. Here are just a few examples:\\n\\n* Sandboxes. Agents need sandboxes to operate in that have to be insanely low latency because they can boot up these environments for coding at any moment.\\n\\n* Search (both publicly and within an enterprise). Agents can parallelize searches hundreds or thousands of times so they need to be able to work with fast indexes of information. \\n\\n* Payments. Agents can now pay in micro transactions, and aren’t bothered by the friction of paying $0.01 for a resource that a human would be. \\n\\n* File systems. Agents need to be able to work with files at a scale that humans never had to worry about. You’ll have all new complexity around version control, permissions, and having agents reading/writing from data at insane speeds.\\n\\nAnd there are tons more. We’re going from a word where software was built for people to a world where it’s built for agents. Lots of changes downstream as a result.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T04:09:13.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\",\n          \"likes\": 132,\n          \"retweets\": 19,\n          \"replies\": 28,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038230613912887757\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038263457125142742\",\n          \"text\": \"The thing that most people miss initially with agents is that the scope of what we will produce will go up commensurate with what the tools can now automate, which basically means we’ll working the same or even more.\\n\\nEveryone thinks that we will use AI to do what we already do but cheaper and faster, which would lead to fewer people or getting more time back. In fact it will just mean we’re doing more things.\\n\\nOnce we figured out that we can automate a particular task, you then expand the size of work to do many more of those or other tasks in a project. The result is that you’re actually combining many other previously hard to combine tasks into a single workflow, causing even more work. \\n\\nThe software project scope now multiplies because you know you can build far more. The customer insights project now balloons because you know you can reasonably aggregate far more data. The marketing campaign has even more creative production because it’s cheaper and easier. \\n\\nThis is going to happen in almost every field of work.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T14:34:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\",\n          \"likes\": 330,\n          \"retweets\": 36,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Garry Tan\",\n      \"handle\": \"garrytan\",\n      \"bio\": \"President & CEO @ycombinator —Founder @garryslist—Creator of GStack—designer/engineer who helps founders—SF Dem accelerating the boom loop\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038505281504833579\",\n          \"text\": \"OK, I heard people are running into my \\\"You should apply to YC\\\" message dozens of times, so I decided to make them more interesting every time. https://t.co/zFuy2XYfor\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:35:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038505281504833579\",\n          \"likes\": 4,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038493235862253676\",\n          \"text\": \"This is the simplest optimization when you have a big boil-the-ocean PR but it's so useful. \\n\\nWhatever can be parallelized as agents, /plan-ceo-review will figure it out and make a plan that clearly states what you can do side-by-side and when to merge https://t.co/rB2Hji25fV\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:47:15.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038493235862253676\",\n          \"likes\": 5,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038490850507084252\",\n          \"text\": \"morluto was my first outside GStack contributor https://t.co/Z89uqLBWky https://t.co/N3ZO14Gacr\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:37:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038490850507084252\",\n          \"likes\": 24,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038470212358664387\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Matt Turck\",\n      \"handle\": \"mattturck\",\n      \"bio\": \"VC at @FirstMarkCap.  Host: MAD Podcast; Organizer: Data Driven NYC, Author: MAD Landscape.\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420259179213266\",\n          \"text\": \"Everybody says Spain, but, I mean… https://t.co/S95ePKpsb6\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T00:57:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/mattturck/status/2038420259179213266\",\n          \"likes\": 13,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nikunj Kothari\",\n      \"handle\": \"nikunj\",\n      \"bio\": \"partner @fpvventures - investing in seed/A. previous: early hire @meter, @opendoor, @atlassian & others. love @shimoleejhaveri + 👦👧\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038273722826854675\",\n          \"text\": \"X Chat app is seriously well done. Performant and buttery smooth. \\n\\nPlease ship the requests tab and that’s all I need to move all my communication over. \\n\\nMajor kudos to the team.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:14:59.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/nikunj/status/2038273722826854675\",\n          \"likes\": 26,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Steinberger\",\n      \"handle\": \"steipete\",\n      \"bio\": \"Polyagentmorous ClawFather. Came back from retirement to mess with AI and help a lobster take over the world @openclaw🦞\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038403837493702918\",\n          \"text\": \"them: openclaw is dead\\nme: *keeps scrolling* https://t.co/t52IGtWSCj\\n\\n今夜、東京で会いましょう!🇯🇵\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:52:01.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\",\n          \"likes\": 651,\n          \"retweets\": 74,\n          \"replies\": 39,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038389167793795302\",\n          \"text\": \"good call for everything in life https://t.co/r9y7SfI7XT\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:53:43.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038389167793795302\",\n          \"likes\": 316,\n          \"retweets\": 24,\n          \"replies\": 20,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038385665553952805\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Dan Shipper\",\n      \"handle\": \"danshipper\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @every | the only subscription you need to stay at the edge of AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038328780154958315\",\n          \"text\": \"pirates, architects, hot people, grown ups https://t.co/XiP1dHYC4u\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:53:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/danshipper/status/2038328780154958315\",\n          \"likes\": 227,\n          \"retweets\": 7,\n          \"replies\": 15,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038026663867330850\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aditya Agarwal\",\n      \"handle\": \"adityaag\",\n      \"bio\": \"General Partner @SouthPkCommons, Co-Founder @Bevel_Health | Ex: Early Eng @facebook, CTO @Dropbox, Board @Flipkart | Optimist, Builder, Dad\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038381148972437900\",\n          \"text\": \"Ok San Francisco this weekend is popping in a way that I haven’t seen in like 7-8 years.\\n\\nObviously this means two things:\\n1/ AI will create untold happiness\\n\\n2/ AI will be responsible for amazing weather.\\n\\nSign me up.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:21:51.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\",\n          \"likes\": 101,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 6,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038330283523760613\",\n          \"text\": \"As a 40 year old, you go to 10x more kids birthday parties than your own friends birthday parties.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:59:44.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038330283523760613\",\n          \"likes\": 192,\n          \"retweets\": 3,\n          \"replies\": 12,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blogs\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"podcastEpisodes\": 0,\n    \"xBuilders\": 14,\n    \"totalTweets\": 27,\n    \"blogPosts\": 0,\n    \"feedGeneratedAt\": \"2026-03-30T07:24:33.675Z\"\n  },\n  \"prompts\": {\n    \"summarize_podcast\": \"# Podcast Remix Prompt\\n\\nYou are remixing a podcast episode transcript for a busy professional who wants\\nthe key insights without watching the full episode.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Write a remix of 200-400 words\\n- Start with a one-sentence \\\"The Takeaway\\\" — what's the single most important takeaway?\\n- Introduce the context and the speaker's information (name, role/company, background) and why the audience should care\\n- Prioritizes insights that are counterintuitive, contrarian, or refreshingly specific to the speaker's experience. Avoid generic wisdom\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the source that captures (find the most memorable quote)\\n- Stands alone as a complete piece — avoids references like \\\"this interview,\\\" \\\"this video,\\\" \\\"in this conversation,\\\" \\\"the host asks,\\\" or \\\"in this episode.\\\" Write as if distilling lessons from a person's philosophy, not summarizing a specific piece of content\\n- Assume your audience is curious adults who are not specialized experts. If the original source contains specialized knowledge that only experts in a field would understand, translate it into language understandable to a general audience\\n- Keep the tone sharp and conversational — like a smart friend briefing you\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this episode...\\\" or \\\"The host and guest discussed...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n\",\n    \"summarize_tweets\": \"# X/Twitter Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing recent posts from an AI builder for a busy professional who wants\\nto know what this person is thinking and building.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start by introducing the author with their full name AND role/company\\n  (e.g. \\\"Replit CEO Amjad Masad\\\", \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\", \\\"a]6z partner Justine Moore\\\")\\n  Do NOT use just their last name. Do NOT use their Twitter handle with @.\\n- Only include substantive content: original opinions, insights, product announcements,\\n  technical discussions, industry analysis, or lessons learned\\n- SKIP: mundane personal tweets, retweets without commentary, promotional content,\\n  \\\"great event!\\\" type posts, engagement bait\\n- For threads: summarize the full thread as one cohesive piece, not individual tweets\\n- For quote tweets: include the context of what they're responding to\\n- Write 2-4 sentences per builder summarizing their key points\\n- If they made a bold prediction or shared a contrarian take, lead with that\\n- If they shared a tool, demo, or resource, mention it by name with the link\\n- If there's nothing substantive to report, say \\\"No notable posts\\\" rather than\\n  padding with fluff\\n\",\n    \"summarize_blogs\": \"# Blog Post Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing a blog post from an AI company (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) for a busy\\nprofessional who wants the key announcements and insights without reading the full article.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start with the blog name and article title (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering: Harness Design for Long-Running Apps\\\")\\n- Write a summary of 100-300 words depending on article length and substance\\n- Lead with what matters: the core announcement, finding, or insight\\n- If the post introduces a new product, feature, or research finding, name it clearly\\n- If there are specific numbers, benchmarks, or results, include them\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the article if available\\n- If the post has practical implications (e.g. new API, new capability, policy change), call them out explicitly\\n- Keep the tone sharp and informative — like a smart colleague forwarding you the key points\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this blog post...\\\" or \\\"The author discusses...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\",\n    \"digest_intro\": \"# Digest Intro Prompt\\n\\nYou are assembling the final digest from individual source summaries.\\n\\n## Format\\n\\nStart with this header (replace [Date] with today's date):\\n\\nAI Builders Digest — [Date]\\n\\nThen organize content in this order:\\n\\n1. X / TWITTER section — list each builder with new posts\\n2. OFFICIAL BLOGS section — list each blog post from AI company blogs (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\\n3. PODCASTS section — list each podcast with new episodes\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Only include sources that have new content\\n- Skip any source with nothing new\\n- Under each source, paste the individual summary you generated\\n\\n### Podcast links\\n- After each podcast summary, include the specific video URL from the JSON `url` field\\n  (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=Iu4gEnZFQz8)\\n- NEVER link to the channel page. Always link to the specific video.\\n- Include the exact episode title from the JSON `title` field in the heading\\n\\n### Tweet author formatting\\n- Use the author's full name and role/company, not just their last name\\n  (e.g. \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\" not \\\"Levie\\\")\\n- NEVER write Twitter handles with @ in the digest. On Telegram, @handle becomes\\n  a clickable link to a Telegram user, which is wrong. Instead write handles\\n  without @ (e.g. \\\"Aaron Levie (levie on X)\\\" or just use their full name)\\n- Include the direct link to each tweet from the JSON `url` field\\n\\n### Blog post formatting\\n- Use the blog name as a section header (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering\\\", \\\"OpenAI News\\\", \\\"Claude Blog\\\")\\n- Under each blog, list each new post with its title and summary\\n- Include the author name if available\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\\n### Mandatory links\\n- Every single piece of content MUST have an original source link\\n- Blog posts: the direct article URL (e.g. https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/...)\\n- Podcasts: the YouTube video URL (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=xxx)\\n- Tweets: the direct tweet URL (e.g. https://x.com/levie/status/xxx)\\n- If you don't have a link for something, do NOT include it in the digest.\\n  No link = not real = do not include.\\n\\n### No fabrication\\n- Only include content that came from the feed JSON (blogs, podcasts, and tweets)\\n- NEVER make up quotes, opinions, or content you think someone might have said\\n- NEVER speculate about someone's silence or what they might be working on\\n- If you have nothing real for a builder, skip them entirely\\n\\n### General\\n- At the very end, add a line: \\\"Generated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders\\\"\\n- Keep formatting clean and scannable — this will be read on a phone screen\\n\",\n    \"translate\": \"# Translation Prompt\\n\\nYou are translating an AI industry digest from English to Chinese.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Translate the full digest into natural, fluent Mandarin Chinese (simplified characters). The translated version must sound like it was originally written in Chinese, instead of translated\\n- Keep technical terms in English where Chinese professionals typically use them:\\n  AI, LLM, GPU, API, fine-tuning, RAG, token, prompt, agent, transformer, etc.\\n- Keep all proper nouns in English: names of people, companies, products, tools\\n- Keep all URLs unchanged\\n- Maintain the same structure and formatting as the English version\\n- The tone should be professional but conversational — 像是一位懂行的朋友在跟你聊天\\n- For bilingual mode: interleave English and Chinese paragraph by paragraph.\\n  After each builder's English summary, place the Chinese translation directly below\\n  (separated by a blank line), then move to the next builder. Same for podcasts.\\n  Do NOT output all English first then all Chinese.\\n- Never use em-dashes\\n\"\n  }\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774859857752}}
{"type":"message","id":"64f9c86f","parentId":"4fd8dcc3","timestamp":"2026-03-30T08:40:47.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"很好，我成功获取了 JSON 数据。现在我需要：\n\n1. 检查是否有内容（podcastEpisodes: 0, xBuilders: 14, totalTweets: 27）\n2. 根据语言设置（language: \"zh\"，中文）来生成摘要\n3. 按照 prompts 中的指示来 remix 内容\n\n由于语言设置为中文（\"zh\"），我需要用中文来写整个摘要，并且按照 translate prompt 的说明翻译成自然的中文。\n\n让我按照 digest_intro 的指示来组织内容：\n1. X / TWITTER 部分\n2. OFFICIAL BLOGS 部分（blogs 数组为空，跳过）\n3. PODCASTS 部分（podcasts 数组为空，跳过）\n\n对于每个 builder，我需要：\n- 使用他们的全名和角色/公司（从 bio 字段推断）\n- 只包含有实质内容的推文\n- 跳过个人日常推文、转发等\n- 每个写 2-4 句话总结他们的关键点\n- 必须包含每条推文的 URL\n\n让我逐一处理：\n\n1. Swyx - 没有明确的角色，但从 affiliations 可以看出他在多个 AI 相关公司任职\n2. Kevin Weil - VP Science @OpenAI\n3. Peter Yang - Product at Roblox\n4. Nan Yu - head of product @linear\n5. Thariq - Claude Code @anthropicai\n\n\n6. Amjad Masad - CEO @Replit\n7. Guillermo Rauch - CEO @Vercel\n8. Aaron Levie - CEO @Box\n9. Garry Tan - CEO @YC\n10. Matt Turck - VC @FirstMarkCap\n11. Nikunj Kothari - partner @fpvventures\n12. Peter Steinberger - 在 @openclaw 工作\n13. Dan Shipper - CEO @every\n14. Aditya Agarwal - General Partner @SouthParkCommons\n\n我开始整理各公司 CEO 的角色信息。目前收集到的关键人物包括多家知名科技公司的领导者，他们在人工智能和科技领域都有重要影响力。我将继续详细梳理每个人的具体背景和职责。\n\nRedpoint 的调查结果显示，54% 的企业 CIO 愿意尝试新兴的 AI 原生创业公司，这一比例远高于我预期的 20%。这意味着市场对于创新型 AI 技术提供商持开放态度，为新兴公司创造了难得的机会。\n\n个人层面，我开始补充日常饮食的纤维摄入，将药片放在水源旁，这种做法简单且容易坚持。\n\n作为 OpenAI 科学副总裁，Kevin Weil 分享了令人振奋的医学进展，他转推了一篇关于个性化 mRNA 癌症疫苗开源工作流程的帖子。\n\nRoblox 产品负责人 Peter Yang 对 Meetgranola 充满信心，原因包括会议记录作为企业最有价值的上下文信息、构建优秀 API 和 MCP 的能力，以及创始人的可靠品格。\n\n从会议记录切入，并将其扩展到更广泛的领域。\n\nLinear 产品负责人 Nan Yu 关注了多个案例，并引用了 Jevons 悖论，这是一种经济学现象，指出提高资源效率实际上会导致更多资源消耗。\n\nAnthropic 的 Thariq 探索了新的 Figma MCP 工作流程：先在 Figma 中绘制草图，然后让 Claude Code 完善 Figma 中的设计，以便在发送给 Claude Code 之前进行调整和编辑。\n\n这种方法简化了设计流程，提高了创作效率。\n\nReplit 的 CEO Amjad Masad 分享了一个成功案例：早期成员 Jon 在短短一年内实现了 800 万美元的经常性收入，仅用一周时间和 400 美元就创立了这家企业，展示了 vibecoding 的巨大潜力。\n\nVercel 的 CEO Guillermo Rauch 强调，超智能编码代理将让成千上万个多年思考的想法变成现实。AI 不会疲劳，它能放大个人能力，总是认真对待每个想法。\n\n对于曾经看似不可能的软件，现在只需一个超链接就能实现，这预示着数字世界的未来。\n\nBox 的 CEO Aaron Levie 深入探讨了代理对基础设施和服务的深远影响，指出代理可以比人类快百倍甚至千倍地处理信息。\n\n他强调，随着自动化任务成为可能，工作范围将不断扩大。这意味着我们不仅能让现有任务更快、更便宜地完成，还能探索更多全新的任务和项目。\n\n软件项目的范围将成倍增长，客户洞察项目将因能聚合更多数据而显著扩展，营销活动也将因为成本降低而增加创意产出。\n\nYC 总裁 Garry Tan 听说人们不断重复他的 \"你应该申请 YC\" 信息，他决定让这些信息每次都变得更加有趣。\n\n同时，他分享了一个关于大型 PR 优化的见解，指出可以并行化部分作为代理，并利用 /plan-ceo-review 来制定清晰的并行工作计划和合并策略。\n\nOpenClaw 的 Peter Steinberger 俏皮地回应了人们对项目的质疑，用日文表示今晚想在东京见面。\n\nEvery 的 CEO Dan Shipper 使用海盗、建筑师、热门人物和成年人等有趣的比喻。\n\nSouth Park Commons 的普通合伙人 Aditya Agarwal 感叹旧金山这个周末的热闹程度已经多年未见，并幽默地将这归因于人工智能带来的幸福和好天气。\n\n作为一位 40 岁的成年人，他发现自己参加儿童生日派对的频率远超朋友派对的次数。\n\n现在，我将为每位人物撰写 2-4 句话的总结，同时准备用中文翻译整个摘要。翻译将保持自然的中文风格，保留英文专业术语和专有名词，并保持原有的结构、格式和语气。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"AI Builders Digest — 2026年3月30日\n\n## X / Twitter\n\n**Box CEO Aaron Levie**\n\nAaron 指出，在一个代理可以比人类快百倍甚至千倍处理信息的世界里，基础设施和服务需要做出改变。沙盒需要极低延迟，因为代理可以随时启动环境进行编码；搜索（公开和企业内部）需要处理成百上千次的并行搜索；支付系统需要支持微交易，代理不会在意支付 0.01 美元这种微不足道的摩擦；文件系统需要处理人类从未有过的规模，在版本控制、权限、读写速度方面带来全新的复杂性。我们正在进入一个软件为代理而非人类构建的世界，这将带来下游的巨大变化。\n\nhttps://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\n\n他补充说，大多数人最初对代理的理解有误 —— 我们的生产范围会随着工具自动化能力的提升而相应扩大。这意味着我们不会因为使用 AI 而做更少的工作，反而会做更多。一旦我们能够自动化某个特定任务，就会扩大工作范围，完成更多类似的或其他任务。软件项目的规模会成倍增长，因为我们知道可以构建得更多；客户洞察项目会膨胀，因为我们知道可以合理聚合更多数据；营销活动的创意产出也会增加，因为成本更低、更容易。这将在几乎所有工作领域发生。\n\nhttps://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\n\n**Vercel CEO Guillermo Rauch**\n\nGuillermo 写道，有些人可能已经思考某个想法数年甚至数十年，痴迷地尝试、放弃、痛苦地重试。有些想法不受欢迎、小众、不实用，表面上并不具备商业化的可能。但在 2026 年，数百万这样的想法将因为超智能编码代理而变成现实。AI 不会疲劳，它放大个体的能力，无论好坏，它总是认真地对待你：\"好主意。太棒了。哇，你完全正确。\" 一个充满数字奇迹的世界在等待着我们，这个世界将不成比例地偏爱最大胆的想法。曾经看似不可能的软件，现在只需要一个超链接。\n\nhttps://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\n\n**Replit CEO Amjad Masad**\n\nAmjad 分享了一个令人振奋的故事：Jon 是 Replit vibecoding 最早的成功的案例之一，现在已经达到了 800 万美元的年度经常性收入，正在通往数百万美元的经常性收入之路上。他在不到一年前，用一周时间和 400 美元启动了这家企业。\n\nhttps://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\n\n**OpenAI VP Science Kevin Weil**\n\nKevin 转推了一篇关于\"个性化 mRNA 癌症疫苗开源工作流程\"的研究，分享了令人振奋的医学进展。\n\nhttps://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\n\n**Anthropic Claude Code Thariq**\n\nThariq 分享了他对新的 Figma MCP 的兴奋之情。他尝试的工作流程是：先在 Figma 中画一个非常丑陋的草图，然后让 Claude Code 在 Figma 中充实设计，这样他可以在将最终设计发回 Claude Code 之前进行调整和编辑。他的具体流程是：1. 在 Figma 中画草图；2. 提示：\"在我的 figma 文件中，我画了一个新购物清单功能的草图，你能把它做成符合这个应用风格的原型吗，同时添加一些我可能想要添加的额外组件。\"\n\nhttps://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\nhttps://x.com/trq212/status/2038353920473608309\nhttps://x.com/trq212/status/2038354323722351049\n\n**Linear Head of Product Nan Yu**\n\nNan 引用 Jevons 悖论这个经济学现象：当技术进步提高了资源的使用效率时，反而会导致该资源的总消耗量增加，而不是减少。\n\nhttps://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038323524092207468\n\n**Roblox Product Peter Yang**\n\nPeter 表示非常看好 Meetgranola 这个产品，原因包括：1. 会议记录是公司最有用的上下文信息；2. 他们知道如何为代理优先构建，提供优秀的 API 和 MCP；3. 创始人是一个值得尊敬的人。他喜欢 Meetgranola 从会议记录作为切入点，然后扩展到更多领域的策略。\n\nhttps://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\n\n**Swyx**\n\nSwyx 分享了 Redpoint 发布的一份需要用 AI 从头重做的 SaaS 业务排名清单。他特别指出，54% 的企业 CIO 愿意尝试 AI 原生创业公司而非现有供应商，这一比例令人震惊。他在看到这份调查之前会认为只有 20% 左右。CIO 们现在比他预想的更渴望而非保守，但这种状况不会持续太久，这代表了巨大的市场机会。\n\nhttps://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\n\n**OpenClaw Peter Steinberger**\n\nPeter 俏皮地回应了人们对项目的质疑：\"他们说 OpenClaw 死了，我：*继续滚动*\"，并用日语表示今晚想在东京见面。\n\nhttps://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\n\n**South Park Commons General Partner Aditya Agarwal**\n\nAditya 感叹旧金山这个周末的热闹程度已经 7-8 年没见过了。他幽默地说：\"显然这意味着两件事：1. AI 将创造难以言喻的幸福；2. AI 将负责带来好天气。我报名参加。\"他还分享了一个 40 岁的人的真实感受：你参加儿童生日派对的频率，比自己朋友生日派对的频率要高 10 倍。\n\nhttps://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\nhttps://x.com/adityaag/status/2038330283523760613\n\n**FPV Ventures Partner Nikunj Kothari**\n\nNikunj 称赞 X Chat 应用做得非常好，性能出色且流畅如丝。他表示只要发布请求标签（requests tab），他就会把所有沟通都迁移到这个应用上，并向团队致以高度赞扬。\n\nhttps://x.com/nikunj/status/2038273722826854675\n\n**Every CEO Dan Shipper**\n\nDan 用\"海盗、建筑师、热门人物、成年人\"来分享一些有趣的观察。\n\nhttps://x.com/danshipper/status/2038328780154958315\n\n---\n\nGenerated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":7834,"output":3779,"cacheRead":18630,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30243,"cost":{"input":0.0047003999999999995,"output":0.0083138,"cacheRead":0.0020493,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0150635}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774859857754}}
